ize=1> I am looking for a group, or several groups of 40  toons to go to Erudin's Crossing.  To help me attain a broken arrow and a gem for a piece of my epic weapon.<br>
<br>
Lots of sharks, they like to feed.  Regular sharks are not that bad, my pet took out at least a dozen by itself with half it's health.  The &quot;Killer Sharks&quot; con blue to me, and they are quite vicious to say the least.  So far, I have not seen them come in groups, singles so far.<br>
<br>
The downside:  I do not know how long it will take for at least 2 of the spirits to spawn, that I need to talk to, to get drops for Epic weapon.<br>
<br>
Upside:  Killer sharks should provide for good exp.  <br>
The other option is to have &quot;Invis to Animals&quot; up, I don't know about anyone else, but I lose my pet when cast on me.<br>
<br>
I do not have any dates scheduled for this excursion.  I will need to see who is willing to go.  I would like to recommend an enchanter to go, if possible.<br>
<br>
Group break down:  Shaman, Cleric, Enchanter, 2 Tanks (Warrior, Ranger, Pally), and a druid (group port out)<br>
<br>
Spells needed: SOW, Levitate, HoS, Enduring Breath (spell or item), invis to animals.<br>
<br>
Objective: Once in location, everyone stays in close, this Name of the test is Patience, I will assume it will take a great deal.<br>
<br>
Time to complete Objective: Several hours -- To give an idea of roughly how long it might take.  The person I turn gem into could take up to two hours to spawn, if not already up.  Then, there are 5 spirits at the bottom of Erud's Crossing, each that spawn one at a time.  Quest guide doesn't give times, if 2 hour spawn time figure at max it could be a bit better than a 12 hour excursion.<br>
<br>
-- Issaketh Shalescale --<br>
